OL,3,CHealth services at 'breaking point' at
OL,4,Cairport immigration centre
OL,6,F"Not enough had been done to make
OL,7,Fclear the distinction between
OL,8,Fimmigration detention and criminal
OL,9,Fimprisonment and, as at the last
OL,10,Finspection, it was clear that the Home
OL,11,FOffice had to reduce the numbers held
OL,12,Fin the centre to relieve pressure on
OL,13,Fcritical services and give staff more
OL,14,Ftime to care for the most vulnerable."
OL,16,FThe length of detention had also risen
OL,17,Fsince the last inspection, with 10
OL,18,Fpeople held at the centre for more
OL,19,Fthan a year and one man held the
OL,20,Flongest period for 519 days.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/11
